  "title": "Senior Accounts Executive / Finance Manager",
  "description": "<h2>Role Overview</h2><p>This role supports day-to-day finance and accounting operations for the Singapore office and acts as the local finance point-of-contact, reporting to HQ Finance in China. The scope focuses on accurate processing, statutory compliance, and timely reporting, with limited transaction volume.</p><h2>Key Responsibilities</h2><p>Daily / Ongoing</p><ul><li><p>Record accounting entries in the accounting system (GL/AP/AR)</p></li><li><p>Monitor bank balances and cash position</p></li><li><p>Process vendor payments and staff reimbursements</p></li><li><p>Verify invoices and supporting documentation</p></li></ul><p>Weekly / Monthly</p><ul><li><p>Prepare payment runs for HQ review</p></li><li><p>Prepare month-end closing schedules and reconciliations</p></li><li><p>Support preparation of monthly management reports for HQ</p></li><li><p>Track receivables and payables</p></li></ul><p>Quarterly / Annual Compliance</p><ul><li><p>Prepare GST returns and supporting schedules (if applicable)</p></li><li><p>Support ECI, corporate tax filings, and IRAS correspondence via tax agents</p></li><li><p>Support ACRA filings, AGM documentation, and XBRL (if applicable)</p></li><li><p>Prepare audit schedules and respond to basic audit queries</p></li></ul><p>Systems & Administration</p><ul><li><p>Maintain accounting system records</p></li><li><p>Manage access to bank portals and government portals (IRAS / CPF / ACRA)</p></li><li><p>Maintain proper documentation and filing of finance records</p></li></ul><p>Risk & Process</p><ul><li><p>Track statutory deadlines and escalate issues to HQ Finance</p></li><li><p>Maintain basic SOPs for key finance processes</p></li><li><p>Highlight risks or anomalies to HQ</p></li></ul><h2>Qualifications & Experience</h2><ul><li><p>Diploma / Degree in Accounting or Finance</p></li><li><p>Min 5 years of relevant experience</p></li><li><p>Speaks & write proficiently in Mandarin to communicate with Chinese colleagues in China HQ.</p></li><li><p>Familiar with Singapore accounting and compliance basics</p></li><li><p>Able to work independently in a small office setup</p></li></ul>",
